@startuml ACE - Request Flow (Example: Post Grade)

autonumber
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor "Professor\n(TEACHER)" as TEACHER
participant "Web Browser\n(React)" as CLIENT
participant "CDN / API Gateway" as GATEWAY
participant "Load Balancer\n(K8s Ingress)" as LB
participant "GraphQL Endpoint\n(Spring Boot)" as GRAPHQL
participant "AuthenticationFilter" as AUTH_FILTER
participant "GradeApplicationService" as GRADE_SERVICE
participant "PostGradeUseCase" as GRADE_UC
participant "StudentRepository\n(JPA)" as STU_REPO
participant "GradeRepository\n(JPA)" as GRD_REPO
participant "Redis Cache" as CACHE
participant "PostgreSQL\nPrimary" as DB_PRIMARY
participant "Message Queue\n(RabbitMQ)" as MQ
participant "Email Service\n(AWS SES)" as EMAIL

' 1. Request
TEACHER -> CLIENT : Click "Lançar Nota"
CLIENT -> CLIENT : Build GraphQL mutation\n(studentId, score, weight, ...)
CLIENT -> GATEWAY : HTTPS POST\n/graphql\nwith JWT token

' 2. Gateway Processing
GATEWAY -> GATEWAY : Validate HTTPS\nCheck rate limits\nValidate signature
GATEWAY -> LB : Forward to service

' 3. Load Balancer
LB -> LB : Select healthy pod\n(round-robin or least-loaded)
LB -> GRAPHQL : Forward request

' 4. Authentication
GRAPHQL -> AUTH_FILTER : Validate JWT token
AUTH_FILTER -> AUTH_FILTER : Verify HMAC-SHA256\nExtract user role\nCheck expiration
AUTH_FILTER -> GRAPHQL : Token valid ✓

' 5. GraphQL Resolution
GRAPHQL -> GRAPHQL : Parse mutation\nValidate schema\nMap to resolver
GRAPHQL -> GRADE_SERVICE : postGrade(command)

' 6. Application Service
GRADE_SERVICE -> GRADE_UC : execute(command)

' 7. Domain Logic
GRADE_UC -> STU_REPO : findById(studentId)
STU_REPO -> CACHE : Try get from Redis\nkey: "student:uuid"
CACHE --> STU_REPO : MISS (not in cache)
STU_REPO -> DB_PRIMARY : SELECT * FROM students\nWHERE id = ?
DB_PRIMARY --> STU_REPO : student row
STU_REPO -> CACHE : Set cache\nkey: "student:uuid"\nTTL: 1 hour
STU_REPO --> GRADE_UC : Student entity

' 8. Validation
GRADE_UC -> GRADE_UC : Validate score (0-10)\nValidate weight (> 0)\nValidate student status (ACTIVE)\nValidate teacher permission

' 9. Grade Creation & Persistence
GRADE_UC -> GRD_REPO : save(grade)
GRD_REPO -> DB_PRIMARY : INSERT INTO grades\n(student_id, score, weight, ...)\nVALUES (?, ?, ?, ...)

DB_PRIMARY --> GRD_REPO : id, created_at, updated_at

GRD_REPO -> CACHE : Invalidate student cache\nDEL "student:uuid"\nDEL "grades:uuid"

' 10. GPA Recalculation
GRADE_UC -> GRD_REPO : findByStudentId(studentId)
GRD_REPO -> DB_PRIMARY : SELECT * FROM grades\nWHERE student_id = ?
DB_PRIMARY --> GRD_REPO : All grades

GRADE_UC -> GRADE_UC : Calculate GPA\nΣ(score × weight) / Σ(weight)\nDetermine status

GRD_REPO -> DB_PRIMARY : UPDATE students\nSET current_gpa = ?,\napproval_status = ?\nWHERE id = ?

' 11. Event Publishing (Async)
GRADE_UC -> MQ : Publish event\n"GradePosted"\n(grade, student, teacher)

' 12. Response
GRADE_UC --> GRADE_SERVICE : grade result
GRADE_SERVICE --> GRAPHQL : success response

' 13. Send Notification (Async - Non-blocking)
MQ --> EMAIL : Process "GradePosted" event\nBuild email\nSend via SMTP

EMAIL --> TEACHER : ✓ Email received\n(Grade notification)

' 14. Return to Client
GRAPHQL -> CLIENT : HTTP 200\nJSON: {\n  "data": {\n    "postGrade": {\n      "id": "uuid",\n      "score": 8.5,\n      "student": {\n        "currentGPA": 8.2,\n        "status": "APPROVED"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}

CLIENT -> CLIENT : Update UI\nShow success message\nRefresh grade list

CLIENT --> TEACHER : ✓ Request completed\n(~200ms total)

note right of TEACHER
  <b>Timeline:</b>
  
  T+0ms: Browser sends request
  T+50ms: API Gateway validates
  T+100ms: Load Balancer routes
  T+120ms: Authentication check
  T+150ms: Business logic
  T+180ms: Database operations
  T+200ms: Response sent
  
  (Email sent in background)
end note

note right of CACHE
  <b>Caching Strategy:</b>
  
  • Student data: 1 hour TTL
  • Grade list: 15 min TTL
  • Invalidate on write
  • Eventually consistent
end note

note right of MQ
  <b>Async Processing:</b>
  
  • Non-blocking email send
  • Automatic retries
  • Dead letter queue
  • Guaranteed delivery
end note

note right of AUTH_FILTER
  <b>Security Layers:</b>
  
  ✅ HTTPS encryption
  ✅ JWT validation
  ✅ HMAC-SHA256 signature
  ✅ Rate limiting
  ✅ RBAC enforcement
end note

@enduml
